  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0d9c\u0dcf\u0dbd\u0dd4 \u0db8\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0daf\u0ddc\u0dbb \u0d85\u0dbb\u0d9c\u0dbd\u0d9a\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0db1\u0dca\u0da7 \u0dc4\u0db8\u0dd4\u0daf\u0dcf\u0dc0\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0d85\u0db8\u0dcf\u0db1\u0dd4\u0dc2\u0dd2\u0d9a \u0db4\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dc4\u0dcf\u0dbb, \u0dc3\u0da2\u0dd3\u0dc0 \u0dc0\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dc1\u0dba \u0d85\u0dad\u0dbb\u0dad\u0dd4\u0dbb BBC \u0db8\u0dcf\u0db0\u0dca\u200d\u0dba\u0dc0\u0dda\u0daf\u0dd3\u0db1\u0dca\u0da7\u0dad\u0dca \u0db4\u0dc4\u0dbb \u0daf\u0dd9\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Brutal attacks by army on Galle Mudoora protesters, BBC journalists attacked during live broadcast",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Early today (22), the security forces brutally attacked the protesters who were staying at the Colombo Fort Presidential Secretariat and the Gota Go village protest ground in Gallumuwadora.",
        "A BBC video journalist was assaulted by the army and one of the soldiers took away his phone and deleted the footage he had recorded.",
        "Jerin Samuel of the BBC Tamil Service who was giving live footage from there; Live footage shows them being beaten by military personnel while repeatedly claiming to be BBC journalists.",
        "However, media organizations and organizations say that several other journalists have been attacked by the military.",
        "It was earlier reported that a large number of security personnel are coming towards the mouth of Galle this morning.",
        "A few hours before the protestors left the President's office, hundreds of army and air force and police commandos surrounded the protest camp set up around the President's office and started pulling down tents.",
        "Regarding the efforts of the security forces to attack the protesters and evacuate them from the place, even before the new President Ranil Wickremesinghe took office 24 hours after the official notification that the protesters would leave the Presidential Secretariat premises on July 22 at 2 pm. Lawyers and civic activists have been heavily questioned.",
        "Many places including the information technology center located in the Gota Go village struggle ground, the disabled warriors' small house, the visually impaired small house have been attacked and destroyed, lawyer Nuvan Bopage and a group of people including Anuranga Shalik, who was disabled due to the attack on May 09. A protester who spoke to BBC Sinhala from there said that he had been taken away by the security forces.",
        "However, at present, no journalist is allowed to enter this area, and the security forces have informed the journalists that they have received direct orders for that.",
        "A few moments ago, the president of the Sri Lanka Bar Association posted a note on his Facebook account and said that \"those responsible for the safety of all should be bound, and using force unnecessarily and brutally is not good for this country and its international image\".",
        "BBC Sinhala's attempts to contact the security forces and the police to inquire about this failed."
      ],
